  "IN:IT": `Indians need a Schengen Type C visa for Italian tourism. Long-stay routes via Italy's Lavoro Subordinato (subject to annual decreto-flussi quotas — Indian agricultural / hospitality workers heavily allocated), Lavoro Autonomo for self-employed, Investor Visa Italy. Substantial Indian community in Italy ~210k — heavy concentration in Punjab-origin agricultural workers in the Po Valley + Bangalore-tech professionals in Milan. India-Italy bilateral mobility supports skilled-worker recruitment.`,
  "IN:ES": `Indians need a Schengen Type C visa for Spanish tourism. Long-stay routes via Spain's Highly Qualified Worker visa (€40,000+ salary), Digital Nomad Visa, Non-Lucrative for passive-income retirees. Substantial Indian community in Barcelona + Madrid + the Canary Islands — Sindhi merchant heritage in coastal Spain runs 100+ years; modern tech / hospitality recruitment also substantial.`,
  "IN:CN": `Indians need an embassy visa for China — applied at Chinese embassy / consulate. Bilateral relations have been complicated since 2020 border tensions but commercial + student mobility continues. Long-stay routes via Z visa (Work — employer-sponsored, Chinese-employer required). Substantial Indian-Chinese commercial relationship via Indian tech professionals at Chinese tech firms (TikTok, Huawei, Alibaba), pharma (Cipla-China, Aurobindo-China), automotive (Tata-China, Mahindra-China).`,

