  "KR:IN": `South Koreans need an e-Tourist Visa for India (USD 25-80, applied online). Long-stay routes via Employment Visa (E-class), Business Visa, OCI for Korean citizens of Indian origin. Substantial Korean community in Chennai + Delhi + Bangalore + Mumbai — automotive (Hyundai Motor India Chennai plant — the largest Hyundai facility outside Korea, Kia Motors India), electronics (Samsung, LG India).`,
  "KR:CN": `South Koreans travel to China — visa-free for 30 days following Nov 2024 expansion. Long-stay routes via Z visa (Work), R visa (high-end talent). Substantial Korean community in Beijing + Shanghai + Qingdao + Yantai (~700k+, the largest Korean community outside Korea historically — pre-COVID peak) — heavy automotive, electronics, trading concentration despite recent decline post-THAAD dispute.`,
  "KR:NZ": `South Koreans travel to New Zealand under the NZeTA (NZD$23, valid 2 years, multi-entry, 3-month stays). Long-stay routes via Skilled Migrant Category, Accredited Employer Work Visa, Working Holiday for under-30 South Koreans (12 months). Substantial Korean community in Auckland + Christchurch (~35k+) — education, hospitality, agriculture (kiwifruit, dairy export to Korea).`,

